		    <refentry id="xarModGetUserMods">
      <refmeta>
        <refentrytitle>xarModGetUserMods</refentrytitle>
      </refmeta>
      <refnamediv>
        <refname>xarModGetUserMods</refname>
        <refpurpose>get list of user modules</refpurpose>
      </refnamediv>
      <refsynopsisdiv>
        <funcsynopsis>
          <funcprototype>
            <funcdef>array <function>xarModGetUserMods</function></funcdef>
            <void/>
          </funcprototype>
          <funcsynopsisinfo>
            <exceptionname>DATABASE_ERROR</exceptionname>
          </funcsynopsisinfo>
        </funcsynopsis>
      </refsynopsisdiv>
      <refsect1>
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>

          <function>xarModGetUserMods()</function> obtains information on
          the modules in this Xaraya system that are active and have a
          user component to them.

        </para>
      </refsect1>
      <refsect1>
        <title>Return Values</title>
        <para>

          This function returns an array of module information arrays if
          the module is found.
          This function returns <parameter>void</parameter> if
          an exception was raised.

        </para>
      </refsect1>
      <refsect1>
        <title>Exceptions</title>
        <para>

          This function raises DATABASE_ERROR if an error occurs while
          querying data.

        </para>
       </refsect1>
      <refsect1>
        <title>Notes</title>
        <para>

          Each module array contains the same set of items as a call to
          <function>xarModGetInfo()</function>
          
        </para>
      </refsect1>
      <refsect1>
        <title>Examples</title>
        <programlisting>
// Get list of available modules with user interfaces
$modarray = xarModGetUserMods();
